Project Name: Correlation of stock sectors to gdp in the United States
Brief Project Description:
We used Python as the language in which we wrote our program.

Our program imports historical stock data and historical gdp data from an api.

It then takes that data and computes yearly growth rates in percentages for both the stock data and the gdp data.

Next, it takes the stock growth percentages and compares them to the gdp growth rate percentages for the same year.

Based on the average difference between the stock growth rates and the gdp growth rates, it computes and prints a correlation coefficient for each stock.

Finally, the program prints the stocks with the highest and the lowest correlations to gdp.
3rd Party Libraries & Assets:
I used numpy, json, and requests. 
I also used Alpha vantage api to fetch json data and I used macro trends gdp growth data(https://www.macrotrends.net/countries/USA/united-states/gdp-growth-rate)

Our main datasets were public published data that came from EPA, US Energy Information Administration, and Nuclear Energy Institute.

Our visualizations and dashboard were created using Tableau.

Project Name: Bike Usage Trends in Comparison to Usage of Other types of Vehicles in America and the U.K. & The Environmental Impact of these Trends
Brief Project Description: We used polynomial regression modelling to forecast usage of bikes in the future and analyze the impacts of mass adoption from a carbon emissions perceptive to determine the importance of bikes in enacting green policy.
3rd Party Libraries & Assets: Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn (particularly the regression plotting feature: seaborn.regplot)

Brief Project Description: Our project is an online website that displays an interactive map along with the top 5 parks to visit in the current month. This list was made by us from a consideration of multiple factors including weather and visitor information. The interactive map allows you to select parks and when selected will bring you to a new page that shows the best months to visit that park based on your weather preferences of rain, and temperature. It also displays a line chart of the current monthly average visitors, along with recommendations of things to do around each park.
3rd Party Libraries & Assets: Streamlit, Pandas, OpenAI, Plotly, Numpy, LeafMap

Brief Project Description:
As high as the skyscrapers of Los Angeles are, so is the crime. 

Los Angeles has a reputation for being one of the most crime-ridden cities in the United States. While the city has made significant progress in reducing crime rates in recent years, it still struggles with a variety of criminal activities, including gang violence, drug trafficking, theft, and property crimes. The city's high population density, economic inequality, and the large number of tourists contribute to the challenges law enforcement faces in maintaining public safety. Despite the efforts of law enforcement agencies and community organizations, crime in Los Angeles remains a serious concern for residents and visitors alike.
